# ReconScanner — Methodology & Design

## Overview

ReconScanner is a custom-built reconnaissance tool designed to automate attack surface discovery during penetration testing.

---

## Features

* Port scanning (Nmap)
* Technology detection
* Directory brute forcing
* JavaScript endpoint extraction
* Web crawling
* Vulnerability probing

---

## Workflow

1. Target input
2. Recon phase
3. Endpoint discovery
4. Parameter extraction
5. Attack surface mapping

---

## Example Usage

```bash
reconscanner target.com --full
```

---

## Purpose

To streamline the reconnaissance phase and assist in identifying high-value attack vectors quickly.

---

## Skills Demonstrated

* Python scripting
* Automation
* Security tooling development
